"{\"abstract\":\"Question answering (QA) in the legal domain has gained increasing popularity for people to seek legal advice. However, existing QA systems struggle to comprehend the legal context and provide jurisdictionally relevant answers due to the lack of domain expertise. In this paper, we develop an Artificial Intelligence Law Assistant (AILA) for question answering in the domain of Chinese laws. AILA system automatically comprehends users\\u2019 natural language queries with the help of the legal knowledge graph (KG) and provides the bestmatching answers for given queries. In addition, AILA provides visual cues to interpret the input queries and candidate answers based on the legal KG. Experimental results on a large-scale legal QA corpus show the effectiveness of AILA. To the best of our knowledge, AILA is the first Chinese legal QA system which integrates the domain knowledge from legal KG to comprehend the questions and answers for ranking QA pairs. AILA is available at http://bmilab.ticp.io:48478/.\",\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"1490519437\",\"name\":\"Weiyi Huang\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/1490519437\"},{\"authorId\":\"119928135\",\"name\":\"J. Jiang\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/119928135\"},{\"authorId\":\"1453998024\",\"name\":\"Qiang Qu\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/1453998024\"},{\"authorId\":\"1768827388\",\"name\":\"Min Yang\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/1768827388\"}],\"citationVelocity\":0,\"citations\":[],\"corpusId\":220480990,\"doi\":\"10.24963/ijcai.2020/762\",\"fieldsOfStudy\":[\"Sociology\",\"Computer Science\"],\"influentialCitationCount\":0,\"is_open_access\":true,\"is_publisher_licensed\":false,\"paperId\":\"159df03ffcd0d840ba937c78ad21e2d0ecc21b64\",\"references\":[{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"39058310\",\"name\":\"L. Sha\"},{\"authorId\":null,\"name\":\"Xiaodong Zhang\"},{\"authorId\":\"145757339\",\"name\":\"F. 